reviews.text:
I don't usually leave reviews for restaurants, but when I do..dos eq..I mean it's usually in fits of anger stemming from the restaurant's hygiene and sanitation. HOWEVER, I just want to say that THIS hot pot place is AWESOME.

First things first, if having the ability to distinguish between "good" and "bad" tasting food is money, I'd be sleeping on park benches. For most restaurants, I would tell you the food is "so-so" because I can't tell either way. That being said, I can really taste the difference in Muhua. This place doesn't have a wide variety of ingredients on its menu, but the quality of its meat is absolutely top notch, especially at this price point. The meat is fresh and tender, nothing like the restructured meat prevalent in many of the lower budget (under $600 TWD per person imo) hot pot places. Usually I feel really thirsty after eating hot pot, but here, I don't get that. On top of that, when you cook the vegetables after the meat, your veggies will have a meaty aroma that tastes a lot better than it sounds. I guess the only thing that could be better is if the restaurant gave you drinks free of charge, but eh, it's not a deal breaker. I'm here for the hot pot, not the coke and juice after all.

So overall, I would highly recommend Muhua if you actually enjoy having high quality meat for your hot pot...without having to hurt your wallet too much. (btw they're moving to Xinyi Breeze Nanshan soon, so if you come here and it's closed, that's why).
